85 (b) The department may collaborate with federal
86 agencies to expedite resolution of customs or licensing
87 barriers.
88 Section 7. (a) The Medical Supply Chain Vulnerability
89 Advisory Board is established and shall:
90 (1) Assess the resilience of critical health care and
91 research supply chains.
92 (2) Recommend policy actions to reduce reliance on
93 vulnerable imports.
94 (3) Issue annual reports to the executive and
95 legislative branches.
96 (b) The board shall consist of five members. There will
97 be one member appointed by each of the following authorities:
98 (1) The Governor.
99 (2) The President Pro Tempore of the Senate.
100 (3) The Speaker of the House of Representatives.
101 (4) The Senate Minority Leader.
102 (5) The House of Representatives Minority Leader.
103 (c)(1) The appointing authorities shall each appoint
104 one initial member to the board for a term of two years.
105 (2) The appointing authorities should work to
106 coordinate their appointments so that there is at least one
107 member from the following groups:
108 a. Supply chain experts.
109 b. Medical professionals.
110 c. Academic researchers.
111 d. Agency representatives.
112 (3) Members subsequently appointed to the board shall
Page 4

(3) Members subsequently appointed to the board shall
