113 each serve a term of four years.
114 (4) The members of the board shall serve without
115 compensation but may be reimbursed for necessary expenses in
116 attending meetings of the board pursuant to the policies of
117 his or her respective appointing authority.
118 (5) The membership of the board shall be inclusive and
119 reflect the racial, gender, geographic, urban/rural, and
120 economic diversity of the state.
121 Section 8. (a) There is hereby created and there shall
122 be a fund which shall be known as the Medical Research Supply
123 Assurance and Trade Resilience Program Fund in the State
124 Treasury for providing grants pursuant to this act.
125 (b) The fund shall consist of gifts, grants, federal
126 funds, or legislative appropriations for purposes of
127 administering the act and providing funding for grants,
128 supplies, and strategic reserve facilities.
129 (c) Amounts in the fund shall be budgeted and allotted
130 in accordance with Sections 41-4-80 through 41-4-69 and
131 Sections 41-19-1 through 41-19-12, Code of Alabama 1975.
132 Section 9. The department shall adopt rules necessary
133 to implement, administer, and facilitate this act.
134 Section 10. This act shall become effective on October
135 1, 2026.
